article.description: Senior Timajh Parker-Rivera posted his third career double-double and Mike Morsell scored 16 to lead Towson past Division III Gallaudet 88-45 Wednesday.
article.headline: Parker-Rivera leads Towson past D-III Gallaudet 88-45
article.linkText: Parker-Rivera leads Towson past D-III Gallaudet 88-45
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Senior Timajh Parker-Rivera posted his third career double-double and Mike Morsell scored 16 to lead Towson past Division III Gallaudet 88-45 Wednesday. Parker-Rivera finished with 13 points, a career-high 13 rebounds and three blocked shots. William Adala Moto and Jordan McNeil scored 14 apiece and Byron Hawkins added 13 points for Towson (3-3). Gallaudet scored 10 straight to take a 10-2 lead five minutes in and led 19-18 with 7:26 left in the first half, but Towson scored 16 of the next 18 and led by 12 at the break. The Tigers made 17 of its first 26 shots in the second half, including a stretch of seven in a row during a 23-7 run that made it 76-39 with 3:57 to play. Trey Gordon scored 13 and Joshua McGriff added 11 points for Gallaudet.
